---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../../site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Test | We Scale Startups"
  description="Run focused growth experiments with clear hypotheses, owners, metrics, and decision rules."
  path="/test"
  metaRobots="noindex,nofollow"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Test</p>
      <h1>Run fewer experiments, learn more from each one.</h1>
      <p>We turn scattered marketing activity into tests with hypotheses, owners, commercial metrics, and decisions the team can act on.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a
          class="button button-dark button-with-subcopy"
          href={siteConfig.bookingUrl}
          data-cta="test-book"
          title={siteConfig.bookingCallReassurance}
        >
          <span class="button-label">{siteConfig.bookingLabel}</span>
          <span class="button-subcopy">{siteConfig.bookingSubcopy}</span>
        </a>
        <a class="button button-light" href={siteConfig.scorecardUrl} data-cta="test-scorecard">
          Or, {siteConfig.scorecardLabel} →
        </a>
        <a class="button button-light" href="/proof" data-cta="test-proof">See proof</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell grid-3">
      <article class="feature-card"><h3>Choose</h3><p>Select experiments by likely learning value, pipeline potential, effort, and risk.</p></article>
      <article class="feature-card"><h3>Measure</h3><p>Use clear leading and lagging metrics so tests do not become activity reports.</p></article>
      <article class="feature-card"><h3>Decide</h3><p>Scale, stop, refine, or transfer the work based on evidence.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="shell cta-inner">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Experiments without a constraint map</p>
        <h2>Name the bottleneck before you scale tests.</h2>
        <p>
          In {siteConfig.bookingCallDurationPhrase}, we can usually tell whether the learning problem is positioning, acquisition, conversion, reporting, or ownership — so experiments compound instead of stacking.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a
          class="button button-brand button-with-subcopy"
          href={siteConfig.bookingUrl}
          data-cta="test-final-book"
          title={siteConfig.bookingCallReassurance}
        >
          <span class="button-label">{siteConfig.bookingLabel}</span>
          <span class="button-subcopy">{siteConfig.bookingSubcopy}</span>
        </a>
        <a class="button button-light" href={siteConfig.scorecardUrl} data-cta="test-final-scorecard">
          Or, {siteConfig.scorecardLabel} →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
